&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Sony Interactive Entertainment?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sony Interactive Entertainment isn’t just the Best Place to Play — it’s also the Best Place to Work. Sony Interactive Entertainment (SIE) is the company behind the PlayStation brand. As a subsidiary of Sony Group Corporation, we’re part of a proud legacy of innovation and excellence. SIE is a dynamic technology company, delivering cutting-edge hardware and network services to more than 100 million people and an entertainment leader, home to some of the most beloved and recognizable intellectual properties (IP) in the world. Our role at SIE is to create and nurture the experiences under the PlayStation brand, a name synonymous with entertainment excellence and creativity.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;PlayStation Studios is seeking a General Manager to join our team. In this role, you will be accountable for the overall business strategy and success of the game. You will make key decisions on strategic, financial, operational, and organizational matters for the game and work to ensure its continued growth and success.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As General Manager, you will be responsible for the operational management, and growth of a interactive digital entertainment game, with a main focus on the day-to-day running of the business and support functions but not involving the direct management of the development and production side of the business.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Essential Functions and Responsibilities:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own end-to-end accountability for the product’s business performance, including financial&amp;nbsp;results, operational outcomes, and long-term sustainability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define success metrics, establish clear performance reporting and review rhythms, and translate&amp;nbsp;results and learnings into informed adjustments to strategy, investment, and operating plans.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure close alignment within the studio by building key rituals and working relationships across the wider studio organization, the global publisher, parent company, and central teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and manage the annual calendar and rhythm of the business, including strategic&amp;nbsp;planning, financial cycles, key stakeholder communications, and decision forums, while aligning long-term strategy, annual objectives, and project timelines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with cross-functional leaders from game development and publishing to set a unified&amp;nbsp;vision and mid-term strategy for the game to deliver on the growth ambition of the product.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Effectively communicate priorities and goals, rallying functional leaders around an aligned&amp;nbsp;strategy, while proactively resolving and adjusting priorities to meet key objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead and guide key internal and external stakeholders across publishing, including Marketing,&amp;nbsp;Sales, and PR, and central publishing groups.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and embed the organizational model by setting up core processes, organizational design, defining key capabilities, and more to ensure the business is run smoothly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;EXPERIENCE&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;15+ years’ experience in general management, including business strategy, organizational&amp;nbsp;design/transformation, HR, financial management and reporting, facility management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Multiple years&#39; experience leading a mid-size studio, game, or publisher.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;• Experience in an Executive Producer or General Manager role for a game is strongly desired.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
